item.description:
Comparing varchar DateTime:
Use &lsquo;&gt;&rsquo; and &lsquo;&lt;&rsquo; operators Example: time &gt;= &#39;2022-07-20T00:00:00Z&#39; Comparing int64 DateTime:
Convert int64 and varchar to timestamp: FROM_UNIXTIME(time/1000) &lt; TIMESTAMP &#39;2022-07-20 00:00:00&#39; Convert int64 to varchar: DATE_FORMAT(FROM_UNIXTIME(time/1000), &#39;%Y-%m-%dT%H:%i:%sZ&#39;) &lt;= &#39;2022-02-13T00:00:00Z&#39;
